Chelsea's English midfielder Callum Hudson-Odoi (C) vies for the ball against Hull City's US defender Eric Lichaj (R) during the English FA Cup fourth round football match between Hull City and Chelsea at the KCOM Stadium in Kingston upon Hull, north east England on January 25, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Chelsea and England winger Callum Hudson-Odoi was arrested at the weekend on suspicion of rape. On Sunday police responded to a report of an unwell woman at his West London apartment. READ: Neymar's mother urges son to 'forgive' rape accuser It was initially believed that the Chelsea player was arrested for inviting the woman over despite ongoing lockdown restrictions but it's now been claimed that the 19-year-old has been accused of rape. Hudson-Odoi was arrested at the scene and later released on bail.